<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/about.css' />
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/footer.css' />
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/secondaryheader.css' />
    <%include templates/meta.ejs%>
    <%include templates/bootstrap.ejs%>
</head>
<body>
<% include templates/navigation.ejs%>
<div class="container-fluid">

    <% include templates/secondaryheader.ejs%>

    <div class="row" id="third">
        <div id="about_title" class="col-md-12">
            <p>About Us</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="fourth">
        <div id="about_pic" class="col-md-12">
            <!-- Background picture implimented in CSS -->
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="fifth">
        <div id="about_p_1" class="col-md-12">
            <h2>Svelar aims to disrupt healthcare by bringing greater transparency, access, and value to users.</h2>
            <!--
            <h2>We are working towards reducing the gap between health professionals and patients so that everyone take their healthcare back in their hands.</h2>
            -->
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="sixth">
        <div id="about_p_2" class="col-md-12">
            <p><b>
                    Would you ever buy a laptop or phone without researching about its features as
                    well as any problems people have experienced with the device? So why would you
                    spend hours on researching something that you will be using only for a few years,
                    but fail to consider a medical product that you may have to live with for the rest of
                    your life?
                </b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="seventh">
        <div id="about_p_3" class="col-md-12">
            <p>
                Svelar is dedicated to creating a space where patients can easily obtain reliable information about the medical products,
                including implantable and wearable devices, as well as peer reviews and references to other resources that will allow the
                patient to make informed decisions.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <% include templates/footerbar.ejs%>
</div>
